This is wrong. The moon's gravity does cause the tides on the side of the Earth facing the moon. But the tide on the other side is not caused because the moon is pulling the Earth away from the water. The moon doesn't orbit the Earth. The moon and earth orbit their common center of gravity, which is deep inside the Earth but offset from the center. So the water on the side facing away from the moon is being flung out by centrifugal force. It's not enough to escape the pull of the earth's gravity but it is enough to reduce its apparent effect on the huge mass of water.
